Development

Being a lead full stack JavaScript developer is three important things...

Web Development

I love being part of product development. I especially enjoy working with the frontend and brining my product owner's vision to life.

API Development

Not all business logic can, or should be handled on the frontend. For these cases a backend is needed to satify requirements. I have these skills as well!

Mentorship

You don't bring full value to your company unless you are sharing your knowledge, encouraging, and empowing those around you to also be their best!

About Me

Work, education, and other useful experience.

  • 2009-2011

    Durham College

    After high school I successfully completed the Electro-Mechanical Engineering Technology Advanced Diploma from Durham College.

  • 2012-2018

    University of Waterloo

    I decided to further my education and get my degree. I enrolled as a Physics major but took an interest classes from ranging from economics, computational science, and biology. I graduated with a general B.Sc. degree.

  • 2018-2019

    Early Career

    After university I started tutoring and even became a math teacher at a private school for some time. This was a convenient role, but my goal was always to get into tech.

  • 2019-Present

    Software Developer

    Made it! Since landing my first role at a chatbot start up I have touched countless technologies finding my passion and specializing in JavaScript/Node.js Full Stack development.
